## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of work in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Work is the bounded structure that connects
actors,
companies,
roles,
tasks,
responsibility,
and outcome-bearing execution.

Work is not just labor presence.
It is the governed relationship between
authority,
assignment,
execution,
review,
and result.

## architectural_position
Work sits between:
- company operational structure
- organization structure
- role assignment
- skill and job semantics
- compensation/economic relations
- market visibility of work opportunities

## required_behavior
- work identity must remain explicit
- assigning authority must remain explicit
- executing actor must remain explicit
- task and scope must remain explicit
- review and closure must remain explicit
- historical work trace must remain preserved

## canonical_rules
- work assignment must not imply unlimited authority
- work result must remain attributable
- review and execution authority must remain distinguishable
- historical work records must remain queryable
- ambiguous work authority fails closed

## state_model
The work domain distinguishes:
- proposed work state
- assigned work state
- active work state
- blocked work state
- review state
- closed work state
- historical work state

## actor_boundary
- assigning authority
- executor
- reviewer
- approver
- adapter

## decision_matrix
- if assignment authority is missing, stop assignment
- if executor scope is invalid, fail closed
- if work exceeds allowed scope, route to review
- if work is closed, preserve historical trace
- if result is disputed, separate execution from approval

## review_checklist
- assignment model is explicit
- execution model is explicit
- review model is explicit
- work lifecycle is explicit
